bilingual.source: You can also buy cheap travel passes.
bilingual.target: 你也可以买便宜的旅行通票。

bilingual.source: It is also a game that is very cheap to play.
bilingual.target: 这也是一项非常便宜的游戏。

bilingual.source: You can stay in a cheap hotel or you can stay with a family.
bilingual.target: 你可以住在便宜的旅馆，或者你可以住在一个家庭。
我买了一件便宜的外套。
这个价格是相对便宜的。
他总是寻找便宜的商品。
你可以在网上购买到便宜的硬件。

bilingual.source: Do you know any cheap hotel nearby?
bilingual.target: 你知道附近有没有便宜的旅馆吗？

bilingual.source: You can find cheap flights on Ctrip.
bilingual.target: 你可以在携程网上找到便宜的机票。

bilingual.source: Do you know where to buy cheap toner?

list.abstract: cheap，英 [tʃiːp]，美 [tʃiːp]。英语单词，作形容词时，指的是无价值的；可耻的；收费便宜的。作副词时，指的是便宜地。短语搭配为“dirt-cheap price（极便宜的价格）”。例句为Besides, underwater cameras are not cheap enough.（此外，水下照相机也不够便宜。） cheap的近义词为inexpensive，ten-cent。反义词为expensive。

yingyinNormal.en: Caroline, you need a cappuccino machine? I can get you one cheap. I know a guy.
yingyinNormal.zh: Caroline 你需要卡布奇诺咖啡机吗？我能给你搞一台便宜的 我有门路。

yingyinNormal.en: When too many cheap mortgages were being sold in 2007, a lot of people didn't know what was going on and a lot of others just followed the crowd.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当许多便宜的抵押品在2007年被贩卖时，有许多人都不知道怎么一回事，而只是跟着大多。数人的步调。

yingyinNormal.en: This family simply wanted a cheap servant.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这户人家只想要个廉价仆人。

yingyinNormal.en: Real estate must be pretty cheap around here. Wow, this is incredible.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这里的房价一定非常低吧！哇哦，真是不可思议。

yingyinNormal.en: It was cheap and plentiful. But nobody knew how to make it into profitable steel.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这些很便宜也很多，但是没人知道怎么把他们做成高效的钢。

yingyinNormal.en: Sure. It's a real job. Not a cheap excuse to keep Mavis happy, so you never leave here.
yingyinNormal.zh: 可以，这是一个真正的职位，不是一个低下的借口让你永远留在这里让梅菲斯开心。

yingyinNormal.en: I got the stuff old look, and I got it really cheap because it's still on that old bottle.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个东西看起来旧旧的，买的时候很便宜，因为放在旧旧的瓶子里。

yingyinNormal.en: Vermont is the first state with a utility that's banking on cow power. But doesn't come cheap.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佛蒙特州是第一个依赖生物能发电的州，但这花费也不少。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, you can just get one of those universal remotes at Radio Shack. they're really cheap.
yingyinNormal.zh: 其实这样一个遥控装置，在瑞帝优上(美国电子产品零售企业)里有买，而且很便宜。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah it is, it is. We really, really have to do something about that. Excuse me, you think I'm cheap?
yingyinNormal.zh: 没错，我们得想个办法。很抱歉，你觉得我很小器？

yingyinNormal.en: So we move the coloreds in and the old ladies move out and I buy their flats cheap. That's what I do.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们让外族裔的人搬进去，那些老太太就不得不搬出来，这样我就能低价买到她们的公寓，我就以此谋生。

yingyinNormal.en: Hello, Cameron. I thought I smelled failure and cheap hair spray. Oh, hello, Martin. You're looking unwell.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好啊，卡梅隆，我就觉得闻到了失败和廉价发胶的味道。好啊，马丁，你看起来不怎么舒服。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, God, nobody likes him, and he's so cheap, he'd never fly to London in a million years. Yeah, invite him?
yingyinNormal.zh: 没有人喜欢他，而且他好小器，他绝不会飞去伦敦的，好，请吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Pizza is an edible snapshot of American food. It's fast, it's filling, and for what you get, it's actually pretty cheap.
yingyinNormal.zh: 披萨是美国食品的一个缩影，它方便快捷,容易填饱肚子，而且非常便宜。

yingyinNormal.en: This is just a cheap trick. I've run a brothel for 10 years, and if there's one thing I know, it's when I'm being fucked with.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不过是个无聊的把戏，我开妓院开了10年，有一件事我绝对相当清楚，就是知道自己被"玩弄"了。

yingyinNormal.en: We are unveiling a new closet today, the Trulhatten. It's Swedish, it's cheap, it's modern. We're gonna grab IKEA by the meatballs.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们今天要发布一款新衣柜，是瑞典产的，便宜，现代，我们要紧握宜家[瑞典品牌]的肉丸[瑞典名吃]。

yingyinNormal.en: Over the last half-century, the food machine made it cheap and easy for us to put away an average of 600 additional calories per person per day.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在过去半个世纪里，食品机器让我们更便宜快捷地 能够额外获得超过600卡的热量，这只是一个人,一天的。

yingyinNormal.en: Highways stretching north from Dallas lured people out to the cheap land and open space of Arlington and other suburbs like this one, Colleyville.
yingyinNormal.zh: 从达拉斯延伸到北部的高速公路引诱着人们离开到这些廉价的土地来，像阿林顿的开放空间和像科利维尔一样的郊区。

yingyinNormal.en: What are corn dogs? Cheap sausages dipped in batter and deep fried. You know, American. Whip something up. Maybe Gusteau in overalls and Huckleberry Tom hat.
yingyinNormal.zh: 什么是炸热狗? 廉价香肠裹上奶油炸得熟透就像美式速食一样，加些东西上去，也许让食神穿工作服戴上帽子。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, Howard, you're a Jew. If there was another wailing wall exactly like the one in Jerusalem, but close to taco stands and cheap prescription drugs, would you still be able to wail at it? Okay, it's definitely me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 霍华德，你是个犹太人，如果有另外一面哭墙和在耶路撒冷的一模一样，不过比较靠近炸玉米卷摊和卖便宜处方药的药店，你还会对着那面墙哀哭吗？好吧，又是我没事找事。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

word_family.mean: adj. 便宜的；无价值的；可耻的；收费便宜的；可鄙的；低廉的；廉价的；用不正当手段得到的；吝啬的

examination_example.sentence: Everything can be done faster and made <highlight>cheaper</highlight>, but there is a cost.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 任何事情都可以做得更快、更便宜，但这是有成本的。

examination_example.sentence: Yet the new system has not yet worked out any <highlight>cheaper</highlight> for the universities.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，对于大学来说，新系统并没有降低任何成本。

examination_example.sentence: By offering on-trend items at dirt-<highlight>cheap</highlight> prices, Cline argues, these brands have hijacked fashion cycles, shaking an industry long accustomed to a seasonal pace.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 克莱因认为，这些品牌低价销售时髦货，从而“绑架”了时尚周期，撼动了这个长久以来以季为周期运转的行业。

word_usage.usage: cheap作形容词时，可用于名词之前，修饰该名词，如：a very cheap price，但其修饰的单词为anything, something, everything等词时，一般用于这些词之后，如：nothing cheap；cheap也可用于系动词之后，如：The shirts were cheap.

sense_info_list.zh: 价格便宜的; 合算的

examination_example.sentence: Staff members of a luxury brand may buy its old stock at <highlight>cheaper</highlight> prices, but they are not allowed to resell them.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 奢侈品牌的员工可能会以更低的价格购买其旧库存，但他们不允许转售这些库存。

examination_example.sentence: In the 1930s, prices crashed, to the point that, in some parts of the country, oil was <highlight>cheaper</highlight> than water.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 20世纪30年代，价格暴跌，以至于在该国的一些地方，石油比水还便宜。

examination_example.sentence: As computer-generated imagery (CGI) has become <highlight>cheaper</highlight> and more sophisticated, the film industry can recreate people on screen一even actors who have been dead for decades.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着计算机生成图像(CGI)变得越来越便宜和复杂，电影业可以在屏幕上重现人物——甚至是已经去世几十年的演员。

sense_info_list.zh: 质量低劣的; 廉价的

examination_example.sentence: Fifteen years ago, Burberry was at crisis point as their signature check pattern was widely imitated by <highlight>cheap</highlight>, imitation brands.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 15年前，巴宝莉(Burberry)正处于危机时刻，因为他们的签名支票模式被廉价的仿制品牌广泛模仿。

word_usage.usage:
cheap不用于修饰价格price。
示例：这顶帽子很便宜。
误 The price of the hat is cheap.
正 The price of the hat is low.
正 The hat is cheap.

cheap表“廉价地”，多与表示“买”(get, buy等)或“卖”(如sell)的动词连用，且置于动词后。
示例：I got this dress cheap in a sale.
这件衣服是我在大减价时便宜买的。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 普通用词, 既可指物美价廉, 又可指价格低但质量却不怎么样。
指商品价格公道, 数量和价格相当。

examination_example.sentence: Even though pumping from these depths is expensive, it is still <highlight>cheaper</highlight> than desalinating (脱盐) the ocean water in the largely coastal state.

examination_example.sentence: The frozen oranges and apples are a little <highlight>cheaper</highlight>, and fruits are really good for the brain.

examination_example.sentence: As solar panels get <highlight>cheaper</highlight>, the world is likely to see more skyscrapers covered in solar panels.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着太阳能电池板的价格越来越便宜，全世界可能会有更多的摩天大楼覆盖上太阳能电池板。
